		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    a guide to da Troll Warrior</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:Horrorlof@hotmail.com">Rorroh</a> | 
		            2/28/2001 3:52:18 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">(I'm not going to speak much Trollish here cuz I've heard it's harder to read. But I'm afraid a little bit may crawl into it, I guez I've been playing diz game too long %-&#163; )<BR>
<BR>
The reason I'm writing diz guide is cuz I saw dere were verry little guides about Trolls, not becuz I know so much about hunting places or someting. Why dere ar so little guides is most likely becuz dere ar so little ppl playing Trollies.<BR>
<BR>
Anyway, first to start off, da gud and bad stuf about being a Troll.<BR>
+High Str and Sta<BR>
+Regeneration (twice dat of normal regeneration)<BR>
+semi-good Agi and Dex<BR>
+good chance for beginners to start Roleplaying<BR>
-Evil (you decide if dats bad or good)<BR>
-bad factions (even with Ogres and Dark Elfs)<BR>
-big race (tuffer to get in dungeons, etc)<BR>
-low cha (you pay more at merchants, but most of the time, it's better to buy from pcs anyway)<BR>
<BR>
Now, about creating.<BR>
This is all up to you, I myself put practically all in Str, and a little in Agi and Sta.<BR>
Str, for more damage, combat skills ar learned faster, and carry capacity, and more chance for doing max damage.<BR>
Sta is very important too (it might actually be better if you put most if not all points into this one, considering that as tank, most of what you'll be doing is tanking. When a monster hits you for 400, it's better to have 50 extra hps den +5 damage)<BR>
Agi, well, more defense, more protection from damage.<BR>
The rest of the stats are of minor importance, at least dats my personal oppinion.<BR>
The god you choose, well, I don't know the entire dark of it, but it matter for factions. Rallos Zek is chosen by most Ogres (and thus could improve their faction slightly) and is not really evil, Inoruuk is chosen mostly by Dark Elves, and Cazic Thule is the God who created the Trollies and the Iksar. My retired Lvl 15 Troll Warrior (Torvonilous) had Cazic (it's perfectly what I am looking for)<BR>
But my lvl 5 Troll Warrior has choses Rallos Zek<BR>
(he is a Warrior, after all) so dat my faction with ogres might improve a bit.<BR>
(I was quite shocked dat, while the manual said that Trolls and Ogres are best friends, the entire city was Dubious to me, but this was probably cuz most quests in Grobb bring yer faction with BrokenSkullClan down)(dats the Ogres I think)<BR>
<BR>
Also you need to decide whether to go for double wield or juzz one 2hander. I went for that last, but most ppls say dubble wield is better, it's your choice.<BR>
<BR>
First, go up to Raynor and give him the scroll, and he will give you an armor. Equip it and the sword, and get your first skills from Raynor (right-click on him) Kick is an extra attack which is additional to your main attack, and should certainly be trained.<BR>
when your ready, put all your often used commands (Main attack, Kick, Taunt, Sense Heading, Sit)in macros to the left and your ready to do some bashing.<BR>
<BR>
Now, for the hunting.<BR>
You start out in Innothule, and I don't find any need to go to Feerot. Start killing Large Rats, Decaying Skellies, Lesser Kobolds, Fungus Spores and Froglok Tads. From low to higher, I'd advice not to hunt the snake/mocasins, unless you got someone with cure poison close by. Stay close to the Bashers (not too close or dey'll steal your kills) and stay close to the border, and you'll hit lvl 2 fairly easy. I never went to left (unless I went to Feerot or Sro) but to the right, the way to Guk. If you do venture left, beware of the high lvl Human bard dat sits next to the wall.<BR>
When you receive Bone Chips (Decaying Skellies), Mushrooms (Fungus Spore) or Froglok Meats (Frogloks) DO NOT SELL DEM. The spores are very rare and you need 4 for a pretty good quest, the Meat is pretty rare too and dere are 2 quests you can use dem for (Oven mittens, 2 handed axe). The gloves are Lore, so only sell dem if you have 3 meets and 10 gp to get yourself new ones. The quest for the axe is good for, the axe (to use it yourself, If you plan on going for 2handeds) den sell the axe for 1 or 2 gp, exp, and faction.<BR>
The bone chips are very valuable for Necros and Sks, a stack of 20 can be sold for 2-5 plat, depending on the area, lvls, and desperatness of the buyer. So keep them untill you get the possiblity to sell dem. You can even (if you have the money) buy them for 2pp from players, and den keep dem to sell em for 4-5 pp. It's your choice. As you gain your lvls, you can start to step on to Frogloks. (always con dem) It's xp, some money, and a chance for armor, which is great.<BR>
Always remember dat in group, you can take on more (and thus better loot), although the xp is divided.<BR>
At lvl5, you can give the Guards of Guk a try. Again, always con dem (both) and remember, taking 2 of dem together is a lot tougher den taking one after the other. A group is a real welcome backup.<BR>
Around lvl 7-8 you can try inside Guk, but only the first room (maybee second too). They may not seem THAT touch, but remember dat a dungeon is a lot more treacherous den outside. If they run away, they most likely will lead you to more and tougher Frogloks, so always be ready to zone.<BR>
When you get to lvl10, (you might want to start thinking about your occupation, you might even start from lvl1 putting points into it)Read Everlore for more info about all the Trade Skills.<BR>
Now is a good time to go to Feerot (Oggok has more equipment for Trade Skills) and you can camp skellies and zombies at ruins and pillars for xp (a little) but mostly for loot. Beware for the Cazic Thule Temple and the Spectres surrounding it. I never came close because they are lvl 35 or 48 creatures, I aint sure.<BR>
For xp, try to get a bind in Neriak, and den you can get some bashing at the zones to Oasis, Nro, SRo (beware of the Mummies dat have disease) and you can camp Derv camps (you need a large party, and it's best if your around lvl 11-13) or Orc Camps in East commons (it's good for faction with Humans) but I didn't, cuz I think the loot kinda sucks. You could also try Lavastorm Mountains, cuz dats real close to Neriak, if you get a bind dere. Camp close to the zone and wait for Drakes mostly, and the occasional Rock Dervish. A party is real welcome, if not neccessary.<BR>
Always try to keep your taunt up (use it even when you're soloing) cuz its one of the most important things when your tanking.<BR>
The xp should come good, and you should quit easily gain a few lvls. When you get 14-15, most of the deserts (except for the crocs, caimans and all) and Lavastorm Mountain are either too easy or too hard (although with a party maybee not)<BR>
and this means it's time to move on to a better area, and get a bind close by (like when you hit 10) What I did was try Befallen, the dungeon in West Commons. Soloing is really dangerous here, try to get in a party. But here was the problem also that most of the undead were green (although they looted lozz of bone chips) and when you go further (you'll also need key, and when you die, the keys are one your corpse, obviously, so you'll either need a party member or other player to open the doors for you) you might get trains on you, which, alhtough they might be green-blue, can hurt you real bad, if not kill you. The Sk npcs dat roam in Befallen have some nice loot (BBC probably the best, if yer a 2hander), but you need a good group to reach dem. It's at this time I quit my lvl 15 Warrior on Torv (together with my neighbour and a friend) and all started on Tallon Vek, becuz of the PvPteams, mainly.<BR>
So here stops my guide, and it wont be updated much until diz new char (currently lvl5) gets up.<BR>
I hope you've gotten some insight, some hints of where to go, and happy hunting!
